name: Act of Authority
text: When Act of Authority enters the battlefield, you may exile target artifact or enchantment.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, you may exile target artifact or enchantment. If you do, its controller gains control of Act of Authority.

name: Aerie Mystics
text: Flying\n{1}{G}{U}: Creatures you control gain shroud until end of turn. (They can't be the targets of spells or abilities.)
flavor: They are cautious with their body language and facial expressions. Any stray movement could betray the positions of the troops they protect and cost many lives.

name: Ajani's Pridemate
text: Whenever you gain life, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Ajani's Pridemate.
flavor: "When one of us prospers, the pride prospers."\n—Jazal Goldmane

name: Angel of Finality
text: Flying\nWhen Angel of Finality enters the battlefield, exile all cards from target player's graveyard.
flavor: "Better the dead depart utterly than be enslaved."

name: Archangel
text: Flying, vigilance
flavor: The sky rang with the cries of armored seraphs, and the darkness made a tactical retreat.

name: Azorius Herald
text: Azorius Herald can't be blocked.\nWhen Azorius Herald enters the battlefield, you gain 4 life.\nWhen Azorius Herald enters the battlefield, sacrifice it unless {U} was spent to cast it.
flavor: "As peace should be—gentle yet unstoppable."\n—Augustin IV

name: Cradle of Vitality
text: Whenever you gain life, you may pay {1}{W}. If you do, put a +1/+1 counter on target creature for each 1 life you gained.
flavor: Naya's trees grow tall and sturdy. Their foliage intertwines to form dewcups, rainwater pools where the elves gather to celebrate life.

name: Curse of the Forsaken
text: Enchant player\nWhenever a creature attacks enchanted player, its controller gains 1 life.
flavor: "Purge the damned, for they have no place among the righteous!"\n—Seeta of Thraben

name: Darksteel Mutation
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature is an Insect artifact creature with base power and toughness 0/1 and has indestructible, and it loses all other abilities, card types, and creature types.
flavor: Infinitely powerless.

name: Eternal Dragon
text: Flying\n{3}{W}{W}: Return Eternal Dragon from your graveyard to your hand. Activate this ability only during your upkeep.\nPlainscycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Search your library for a Plains card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.)

name: Fiend Hunter
text: When Fiend Hunter enters the battlefield, you may exile another target creature.\nWhen Fiend Hunter leaves the battlefield, return the exiled card to the battlefield under its owner's control.

name: Flickerform
text: Enchant creature\n{2}{W}{W}: Exile enchanted creature and all Auras attached to it. At the beginning of the next end step, return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control. If you do, return the other cards exiled this way to the battlefield under their owners' control attached to that creature.

name: Flickerwisp
text: Flying\nWhen Flickerwisp enters the battlefield, exile another target permanent. Return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control at the beginning of the next end step.
flavor: Its wings disturb more than air.

name: Karmic Guide
text: Flying, protection from black\nEcho {3}{W}{W} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)\nWhen Karmic Guide enters the battlefield, return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.

name: Kirtar's Wrath
text: Destroy all creatures. They can't be regenerated.\nThreshold — If seven or more cards are in your graveyard, instead destroy all creatures, then put two 1/1 white Spirit creature tokens with flying onto the battlefield. Creatures destroyed this way can't be regenerated.

name: Kongming, "Sleeping Dragon"
text: Other creatures you control get +1/+1.
flavor: "Such a lord as this—all virtues' height—Had never been, nor ever was again."

name: Mirror Entity
text: Changeling (This card is every creature type.)\n{X}: Until end of turn, creatures you control have base power and toughness X/X and gain all creature types.
flavor: Unaware of Lorwyn's diversity, it sees only itself, reflected a thousand times over.

name: Mystic Barrier
text: When Mystic Barrier enters the battlefield or at the beginning of your upkeep, choose left or right.\nEach player may attack only the opponent seated nearest him or her in the last chosen direction and planeswalkers controlled by that player.

name: Razor Hippogriff
text: Flying\nWhen Razor Hippogriff enters the battlefield, return target artifact card from your graveyard to your hand. You gain life equal to that card's converted mana cost.
flavor: She incubates her eggs in gold and mana.

name: Serene Master
text: Whenever Serene Master blocks, exchange its power and the power of target creature it's blocking until end of combat.
flavor: "A great warrior studies many different disciplines and takes the best from each."\n—Gideon Jura

name: Serra Avatar
text: Serra Avatar's power and toughness are each equal to your life total.\nWhen Serra Avatar is put into a graveyard from anywhere, shuffle it into its owner's library.
flavor: "Serra isn't dead. She lives on through me."

name: Stonecloaker
text:
Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)
Flying
When Stonecloaker enters the battlefield, return a creature you control to its owner's hand.
When Stonecloaker enters the battlefield, exile target card from a graveyard.

name: Survival Cache
text: You gain 2 life. Then if you have more life than an opponent, draw a card.\nRebound (If you cast this spell from your hand, exile it as it resolves. At the beginning of your next upkeep, you may cast this card from exile without paying its mana cost.)

name: Tempt with Glory
text: Tempting offer — Put a +1/+1 counter on each creature you control. Each opponent may put a +1/+1 counter on each creature he or she controls. For each opponent who does, put a +1/+1 counter on each creature you control.

name: Unexpectedly Absent
text: Put target nonland permanent into its owner's library just beneath the top X cards of that library.
flavor: Once you've been dragged down the currents of time, you'll never quite trust your own permanence again.

name: Wall of Reverence
text: Defender, flying\nAt the beginning of your end step, you may gain life equal to the power of target creature you control.
flavor: The lives of elves are long, but their memories are longer. Even after death, they do not desert their homes.

name: Wrath of God
text: Destroy all creatures. They can't be regenerated.

name: Arcane Denial
text: Counter target spell. Its controller may draw up to two cards at the beginning of the next turn's upkeep.\nYou draw a card at the beginning of the next turn's upkeep.

name: Arcane Melee
text: Instant and sorcery spells cost {2} less to cast.
flavor: Debates between wizards are never purely academic.

name: Augur of Bolas
text: When Augur of Bolas enters the battlefield, look at the top three cards of your library. You may reveal an instant or sorcery card from among them and put it into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Azami, Lady of Scrolls
text: Tap an untapped Wizard you control: Draw a card.
flavor: "Choices belong to those with the luxuries of time and distance. We have neither. I recommend we proceed with the plan to destroy all shrines of the kami."\n—Lady Azami, letter to Sensei Hisoka

name: Blue Sun's Zenith
text: Target player draws X cards. Shuffle Blue Sun's Zenith into its owner's library.
flavor: "The Origin Query will wait. We must ensure we survive to return to it."\n—Pelyus, vedalken ordinar

name: Borrowing 100,000 Arrows
text: Draw a card for each tapped creature target opponent controls.
flavor: Kongming and Lu Su tricked Wei troops into shooting over 100,000 arrows at them to later use against the Wei at Red Cliffs.

name: Brilliant Plan
text: Draw three cards.
flavor: At Red Cliffs, Kongming and Zhou Yu each wrote his plan for defeating Wei on the palm of his hand. They laughed as they both revealed the same word, "Fire."

name: Control Magic
text: Enchant creature\nYou control enchanted creature.
flavor: "Do as I think, not as I do."\n—Jace Beleren

name: Curse of Inertia
text: Enchant player\nWhenever a player attacks enchanted player with one or more creatures, that attacking player may tap or untap target permanent of his or her choice.
flavor: "As long as I pull the strings, you will dance."\n—Tezzeret

name: Deceiver Exarch
text:
Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)
When Deceiver Exarch enters the battlefield, choose one —
• Untap target permanent you control.
• Tap target permanent an opponent controls.

name: Deep Analysis
text: Target player draws two cards.\nFlashback—{1}{U}, Pay 3 life. (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
flavor: "The specimen seems to be broken."

name: Dismiss
text: Counter target spell.\nDraw a card.
flavor: "There is nothing you can do that I cannot simply deny."\n—Ertai, wizard adept

name: Diviner Spirit
text: Whenever Diviner Spirit deals combat damage to a player, you and that player each draw that many cards.
flavor: Sentience is its natural habitat.

name: Djinn of Infinite Deceits
text: Flying\n{T}: Exchange control of two target nonlegendary creatures. You can't activate this ability during combat.
flavor: The winds of change have a mind of their own.

name: Dungeon Geists
text: Flying\nWhen Dungeon Geists enters the battlefield, tap target creature an opponent controls. That creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step for as long as you control Dungeon Geists.

name: Echo Mage
text:
Level up {1}{U} ({1}{U}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 2-3
2/4
{U}{U}, {T}: Copy target instant or sorcery spell. You may choose new targets for the copy.
LEVEL 4+
2/5
{U}{U}, {T}: Copy target instant or sorcery spell twice. You may choose new targets for the copies.

name: Fog Bank
text: Defender, flying\nPrevent all combat damage that would be dealt to and dealt by Fog Bank.
flavor: "The union of sea and sky makes a perfect cover."\n—Talrand, sky summoner

name: Guard Gomazoa
text: Defender, flying\nPrevent all combat damage that would be dealt to Guard Gomazoa.
flavor: It lingers near the outposts of the Makindi Trenches, inadvertently granting another layer of defense.

name: Hada Spy Patrol
text:
Level up {2}{U} ({2}{U}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 1-2
2/2
Hada Spy Patrol can't be blocked.
LEVEL 3+
3/3
Shroud (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
Hada Spy Patrol can't be blocked.

name: Illusionist's Gambit
text: Cast Illusionist's Gambit only during the declare blockers step on an opponent's turn.\nRemove all attacking creatures from combat and untap them. After this phase, there is an additional combat phase. Each of those creatures attacks that combat if able. They can't attack you or a planeswalker you control that combat.

name: Jace's Archivist
text: {U}, {T}: Each player discards his or her hand, then draws cards equal to the greatest number of cards a player discarded this way.
flavor: "This is a sacred duty. Master Beleren's trust has bought an eternity of my loyalty."

name: Lu Xun, Scholar General
text: Horsemanship (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with horsemanship.)\nWhenever Lu Xun, Scholar General deals damage to an opponent, you may draw a card.

name: Mnemonic Wall
text: Defender\nWhen Mnemonic Wall enters the battlefield, you may return target instant or sorcery card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: "I'd build an entire fortress of them if I could."\n—Mzali, Lighthouse archmage

name: Opportunity
text: Target player draws four cards.
flavor: "Opportunity isn't something you wait for. It's something you create."

name: Order of Succession
text: Choose left or right. Starting with you and proceeding in the chosen direction, each player chooses a creature controlled by the next player in that direction. Each player gains control of the creature he or she chose.
flavor: "Long live . . . me."

name: Propaganda
text: Creatures can't attack you unless their controller pays {2} for each creature he or she controls that's attacking you.
flavor: "The cost of your opposition will be extracted from your wits."\n—Nekusar, the Mindrazer

name: Prosperity
text: Each player draws X cards.
flavor: "True riches are found in the mazes of the mind."\n—Tamiyo, the Moon Sage

name: Raven Familiar
text: Flying\nEcho {2}{U} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)\nWhen Raven Familiar enters the battlefield, look at the top three cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Sharding Sphinx
text: Flying\nWhenever an artifact creature you control deals combat damage to a player, you may put a 1/1 blue Thopter artifact creature token with flying onto the battlefield.
flavor: Whether mechanical or biological, life finds a way to propagate itself.

name: Skyscribing
text: Each player draws X cards.\nForecast — {2}{U}, Reveal Skyscribing from your hand: Each player draws a card. (Activate this ability only during your upkeep and only once each turn.)
flavor: "All clouds should be so organized."\n—Isperia

name: Stormscape Battlemage
text: Kicker {W} and/or {2}{B}\nWhen Stormscape Battlemage enters the battlefield, if it was kicked with its {W} kicker, you gain 3 life.\nWhen Stormscape Battlemage enters the battlefield, if it was kicked with its {2}{B} kicker, destroy target nonblack creature. That creature can't be regenerated.

name: Strategic Planning
text: Look at the top three cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the rest into your graveyard.
flavor: "Plans evolved within the tent decide a victory 1,000 li away."

name: Tempt with Reflections
text: Tempting offer — Choose target creature you control. Put a token onto the battlefield that's a copy of that creature. Each opponent may put a token onto the battlefield that's a copy of that creature. For each opponent who does, put a token onto the battlefield that's a copy of that creature.

name: Thornwind Faeries
text: Flying\n{T}: Thornwind Faeries deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Guarding the ship is the Thornwinds' first concern. Getting along with the locals ranks fourth or fifth at best.

name: Tidal Force
text: At the beginning of each upkeep, you may tap or untap target permanent.
flavor: "Do not speak the name of the sea, for if it should hear you and rise up, no fortress in the world could hide you."\n—Gimara of Halimar

name: True-Name Nemesis
text: As True-Name Nemesis enters the battlefield, choose a player.\nTrue-Name Nemesis has protection from the chosen player. (This creature can't be blocked, targeted, dealt damage, or enchanted by anything controlled by that player.)

name: Uyo, Silent Prophet
text: Flying\n{2}, Return two lands you control to their owner's hand: Copy target instant or sorcery spell. You may choose new targets for the copy.

name: Vision Skeins
text: Each player draws two cards.
flavor: "I could see in the other mage's eyes that he'd thought of it too. Then it became a race to exploit the knowledge first."

name: Wash Out
text: Return all permanents of the color of your choice to their owners' hands.
flavor: "It's not the darkness I fear but dull and numbing shades of gray."\n—Sydri, galvanic genius

name: Wonder
text: Flying\nAs long as Wonder is in your graveyard and you control an Island, creatures you control have flying.
flavor: "The awestruck birds gazed at Wonder. Slowly, timidly, they rose into the air."\n—Scroll of Beginnings

name: Annihilate
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.\nDraw a card.
flavor: "Whatever Yawgmoth marks, dies. There is no escape."\n—Tsabo Tavoc, Phyrexian general

name: Army of the Damned
text: Put thirteen 2/2 black Zombie creature tokens onto the battlefield tapped.\nFlashback {7}{B}{B}{B} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
flavor: Sometimes death comes knocking. Sometimes it tears down the walls.

name: Baleful Force
text: At the beginning of each upkeep, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
flavor: "As with any malevolent being, the trick is knowing how long you can afford to keep it in your service."\n—Liliana Vess

name: Curse of Shallow Graves
text: Enchant player\nWhenever a player attacks enchanted player with one or more creatures, that attacking player may put a 2/2 black Zombie creature token onto the battlefield tapped.

name: Decree of Pain
text: Destroy all creatures. They can't be regenerated. Draw a card for each creature destroyed this way.\nCycling {3}{B}{B} ({3}{B}{B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nWhen you cycle Decree of Pain, all creatures get -2/-2 until end of turn.

name: Dirge of Dread
text: All creatures gain fear until end of turn. (They can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\nCycling {1}{B} ({1}{B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nWhen you cycle Dirge of Dread, you may have target creature gain fear until end of turn.

name: Disciple of Griselbrand
text: {1}, Sacrifice a creature: You gain life equal to the sacrificed creature's toughness.
flavor: The demon Griselbrand dared to stand against Avacyn, earning him the loathing of thousands and the admiration of a few.

name: Endless Cockroaches
text: When Endless Cockroaches dies, return it to its owner's hand.
flavor: There is nothing more repulsive than a cockroach—except a cockroach and all its friends.

name: Endrek Sahr, Master Breeder
text: Whenever you cast a creature spell, put X 1/1 black Thrull creature tokens onto the battlefield, where X is that spell's converted mana cost.\nWhen you control seven or more Thrulls, sacrifice Endrek Sahr, Master Breeder.

name: Famine
text: Famine deals 3 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: "Better to starve to death than be bored to death."\n—Liliana Vess

name: Fell Shepherd
text: Whenever Fell Shepherd deals combat damage to a player, you may return to your hand all creature cards that were put into your graveyard from the battlefield this turn.\n{B}, Sacrifice another creature: Target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.

name: Greed
text: {B}, Pay 2 life: Draw a card.
flavor: What is a sliver of one's soul compared to unimaginable wealth?

name: Hooded Horror
text: Hooded Horror can't be blocked as long as defending player controls the most creatures or is tied for the most.
flavor: Insidious fear can be the undoing of the greatest of armies.

name: Infest
text: All creatures get -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor: "This is why we don't go out in banewasp weather."\n—Rannon, Vithian holdout

name: Marrow Bats
text: Flying\nPay 4 life: Regenerate Marrow Bats.
flavor: "No matter how far we push into Stensia, undeath will always remain in these lands."\n—Terhold, archmage of Drunau

name: Nightscape Familiar
text: Blue spells and red spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.\n{1}{B}: Regenerate Nightscape Familiar.
flavor: Nightscape masters don't stop at raising the spirit of a fallen battlemage. They raise the flesh along with it.

name: Ophiomancer
text: At the beginning of each upkeep, if you control no Snakes, put a 1/1 black Snake creature token with deathtouch onto the battlefield.
flavor: "There are dark, ancient arts that fascinate even me."\n—Sorin Markov

name: Phthisis
text: Destroy target creature. Its controller loses life equal to its power plus its toughness.\nSuspend 5—{1}{B} (Rather than cast this card from your hand, you may pay {1}{B} and exile it with five time counters on it. At the beginning of your upkeep, remove a time counter. When the last is removed, cast it without paying its mana cost.)

name: Phyrexian Delver
text: When Phyrexian Delver enters the battlefield, return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. You lose life equal to that card's converted mana cost.
flavor: Because the dead have no will to resist.

name: Phyrexian Gargantua
text: When Phyrexian Gargantua enters the battlefield, you draw two cards and you lose 2 life.
flavor: Other Phyrexians have nightmares about the gargantua.

name: Phyrexian Reclamation
text: {1}{B}, Pay 2 life: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Death is no excuse to stop working.

name: Price of Knowledge
text: Players have no maximum hand size.\nAt the beginning of each opponent's upkeep, Price of Knowledge deals damage to that player equal to the number of cards in that player's hand.

name: Quagmire Druid
text: {G}, {T}, Sacrifice a creature: Destroy target enchantment.
flavor: As the druids had devoted their lives to preserving Dominaria, so did they devote their deaths.

name: Reckless Spite
text: Destroy two target nonblack creatures. You lose 5 life.
flavor: "The end is justified in being mean. Or something like that."

name: Sanguine Bond
text: Whenever you gain life, target opponent loses that much life.
flavor: "Blood is constant. Every drop I drink, someone must bleed."\n—Vradeen, vampire nocturnus

name: Stronghold Assassin
text: {T}, Sacrifice a creature: Destroy target nonblack creature.
flavor: The assassin sees only throats and hears only heartbeats.

name: Sudden Spoiling
text: Split second (As long as this spell is on the stack, players can't cast spells or activate abilities that aren't mana abilities.)\nUntil end of turn, creatures target player controls lose all abilities and have base power and toughness 0/2.

name: Tempt with Immortality
text: Tempting offer — Return a creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. Each opponent may return a creature card from his or her graveyard to the battlefield. For each player who does, return a creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.

name: Toxic Deluge
text: As an additional cost to cast Toxic Deluge, pay X life.\nAll creatures get -X/-X until end of turn.
flavor: "It's a difficult task to quarantine a plague that moves with the clouds."\n—Esara, healer adept

name: Vampire Nighthawk
text: Flying\nDeathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)\nLifelink (Damage dealt by this creature also causes you to gain that much life.)

name: Vile Requiem
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you may put a verse counter on Vile Requiem.\n{1}{B}, Sacrifice Vile Requiem: Destroy up to X target nonblack creatures, where X is the number of verse counters on Vile Requiem. They can't be regenerated.

name: Viscera Seer
text: Sacrifice a creature: Scry 1. (Look at the top card of your library. You may put that card on the bottom of your library.)
flavor: In matters of life and death, he trusts his gut.

name: Wight of Precinct Six
text: Wight of Precinct Six gets +1/+1 for each creature card in your opponents' graveyards.
flavor: Even the lost and undead need a protector.

name: Blood Rites
text: {1}{R}, Sacrifice a creature: Blood Rites deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: In war, the best leaders are open to all tactics.

name: Capricious Efreet
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, choose target nonland permanent you control and up to two target nonland permanents you don't control. Destroy one of them at random.
flavor: "You wish for great destruction? It is done, my master."

name: Charmbreaker Devils
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, return an instant or sorcery card at random from your graveyard to your hand.\nWhenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, Charmbreaker Devils gets +4/+0 until end of turn.

name: Crater Hellion
text: Echo {4}{R}{R} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)\nWhen Crater Hellion enters the battlefield, it deals 4 damage to each other creature.

name: Curse of Chaos
text: Enchant player\nWhenever a player attacks enchanted player with one or more creatures, that attacking player may discard a card. If the player does, he or she draws a card.
flavor: "Let them cry for mercy. The only one who can hear them is me."\n—Siglind the Conqueror

name: Fireball
text: Fireball deals X damage divided evenly, rounded down, among any number of target creatures and/or players.\nFireball costs {1} more to cast for each target beyond the first.

name: Fissure Vent
text: Choose one or both —\n• Destroy target artifact.\n• Destroy target nonbasic land.
flavor: "Something down there has an appetite for what we're standing on. Let's hope it doesn't want seconds."\n—Samila, Murasa Expeditionary House

name: From the Ashes
text: Destroy all nonbasic lands. For each land destroyed this way, its controller may search his or her library for a basic land card and put it onto the battlefield. Then each player who searched his or her library this way shuffles it.

name: Furnace Celebration
text: Whenever you sacrifice another permanent, you may pay {2}. If you do, Furnace Celebration deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Nothing impresses goblins more than something that's bound to kill them.

name: Goblin Bombardment
text: Sacrifice a creature: Goblin Bombardment deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: One mogg to aim the catapult, one mogg to steer the rock.

name: Goblin Sharpshooter
text: Goblin Sharpshooter doesn't untap during your untap step.\nWhenever a creature dies, untap Goblin Sharpshooter.\n{T}: Goblin Sharpshooter deals 1 damage to target creature or player.

name: Guttersnipe
text: Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, Guttersnipe deals 2 damage to each opponent.
flavor: He wants to watch Ravnica burn, one soul at a time.

name: Incendiary Command
text:
Choose two —
• Incendiary Command deals 4 damage to target player.
• Incendiary Command deals 2 damage to each creature.
• Destroy target nonbasic land.
• Each player discards all the cards in his or her hand, then draws that many cards.

name: Inferno Titan
text: {R}: Inferno Titan gets +1/+0 until end of turn.\nWhenever Inferno Titan enters the battlefield or attacks, it deals 3 damage divided as you choose among one, two, or three target creatures and/or players.

name: Magus of the Arena
text: {3}, {T}: Tap target creature you control and target creature of an opponent's choice he or she controls. Those creatures fight each other. (Each deals damage equal to its power to the other.)
flavor: The magus still hears the roar of the crowds. They're gone, but the will to compete remains.

name: Mass Mutiny
text: For each opponent, gain control of up to one target creature that player controls until end of turn. Untap those creatures. They gain haste until end of turn.
flavor: "What say you, my most trusted advisors? . . . Advisors?"\n—Edra, merfolk sovereign

name: Molten Disaster
text: Kicker {R} (You may pay an additional {R} as you cast this spell.)\nIf Molten Disaster was kicked, it has split second. (As long as this spell is on the stack, players can't cast spells or activate abilities that aren't mana abilities.)\nMolten Disaster deals X damage to each creature without flying and each player.

name: Rough
text: Rough deals 2 damage to each creature without flying.

name: Tumble
text: Tumble deals 6 damage to each creature with flying.

name: Slice and Dice
text: Slice and Dice deals 4 damage to each creature.\nCycling {2}{R} ({2}{R}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nWhen you cycle Slice and Dice, you may have it deal 1 damage to each creature.

name: Spitebellows
text: When Spitebellows leaves the battlefield, it deals 6 damage to target creature.\nEvoke {1}{R}{R} (You may cast this spell for its evoke cost. If you do, it's sacrificed when it enters the battlefield.)
flavor: Disaster stalks with gaping jaws across unready lands.

name: Stalking Vengeance
text: Haste\nWhenever another creature you control dies, it deals damage equal to its power to target player.
flavor: Something roams the killing places, sniffing the guilt of the slayers, stalking them on iron paws.

name: Starstorm
text: Starstorm deals X damage to each creature.\nCycling {3} ({3}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
flavor: Ever since the disaster, the city's survivors viewed the star-strewn sky with dread.

name: Street Spasm
text: Street Spasm deals X damage to target creature without flying you don't control.\nOverload {X}{X}{R}{R} (You may cast this spell for its overload cost. If you do, change its text by replacing all instances of "target" with "each.")

name: Sudden Demise
text: Choose a color. Sudden Demise deals X damage to each creature of the chosen color.
flavor: In the Skyfang Mountains, one misstep can mean the end of an entire clan.

name: Tempt with Vengeance
text: Tempting offer — Put X 1/1 red Elemental creature tokens with haste onto the battlefield. Each opponent may put X 1/1 red Elemental creature tokens with haste onto the battlefield. For each player who does, put X 1/1 red Elemental creature tokens with haste onto the battlefield.

name: Terra Ravager
text: Whenever Terra Ravager attacks, it gets +X/+0 until end of turn, where X is the number of lands defending player controls.
flavor: It lives in the mountaintops, feeds at the mountains' feet, and kills anything it finds on the path between.

name: Tooth and Claw
text: Sacrifice two creatures: Put a 3/1 red Beast creature token named Carnivore onto the battlefield.
flavor: "You deify nature as female—kind and gentle—yet you cringe at what is natural."\n—Mirri of the Weatherlight

name: War Cadence
text: {X}{R}: This turn, creatures can't block unless their controller pays {X} for each blocking creature he or she controls.
flavor: The rhythm isn't a call to arms, but a signal that the goblins have made a new enemy.

name: Warstorm Surge
text: Whenever a creature enters the battlefield under your control, it deals damage equal to its power to target creature or player.
flavor: "Listen to the roar! Feel the thunder! The Immersturm shouts its approval with every bolt of lightning!"

name: Where Ancients Tread
text: Whenever a creature with power 5 or greater enters the battlefield under your control, you may have Where Ancients Tread deal 5 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "Never subtle nor cryptic is the reckoning of the mighty."\n—Mayael the Anima

name: Widespread Panic
text: Whenever a spell or ability causes its controller to shuffle his or her library, that player puts a card from his or her hand on top of his or her library.
flavor: "How thin is the veneer of civilization! A modest measure of panic will wash it off completely."\n—Guard Erdrud of An Karras

name: Wild Ricochet
text: You may choose new targets for target instant or sorcery spell. Then copy that spell. You may choose new targets for the copy.
flavor: "May your day never match your expectations."\n—Scriptus Fleen, flectomancer

name: Witch Hunt
text: Players can't gain life.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, Witch Hunt deals 4 damage to you.\nAt the beginning of your end step, target opponent chosen at random gains control of Witch Hunt.
flavor: The accusations spread like hungry flames.

name: Acidic Slime
text: Deathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)\nWhen Acidic Slime enters the battlefield, destroy target artifact, enchantment, or land.

name: Avenger of Zendikar
text: When Avenger of Zendikar enters the battlefield, put a 0/1 green Plant creature token onto the battlefield for each land you control.\nLandfall — Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, you may put a +1/+1 counter on each Plant creature you control.

name: Baloth Woodcrasher
text: Landfall — Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, Baloth Woodcrasher gets +4/+4 and gains trample until end of turn.
flavor: Its insatiable hunger quickly depletes a region of prey. It must migrate from place to place to feed its massive bulk.

name: Bane of Progress
text: When Bane of Progress enters the battlefield, destroy all artifacts and enchantments. Put a +1/+1 counter on Bane of Progress for each permanent destroyed this way.
flavor: It sees shaped stone and carved wood as mutilations.

name: Brooding Saurian
text: At the beginning of each end step, each player gains control of all nontoken permanents he or she owns.
flavor: "I have been trapped in the lizard's lair for days. It seems to regard me as its child and will not let me leave."\n—Aevar Borg, northern guide, journal entry

name: Cultivate
text: Search your library for up to two basic land cards, reveal those cards, and put one onto the battlefield tapped and the other into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: All seeds share a common bond, calling to each other across infinity.

name: Curse of Predation
text: Enchant player\nWhenever a creature attacks enchanted player, put a +1/+1 counter on it.
flavor: "Hunters feed on the fear of their prey."\n—Garruk Wildspeaker

name: Deadwood Treefolk
text: Vanishing 3 (This creature enters the battlefield with three time counters on it. At the beginning of your upkeep, remove a time counter from it. When the last is removed, sacrifice it.)\nWhen Deadwood Treefolk enters the battlefield or leaves the battlefield, return another target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.

name: Drumhunter
text: At the beginning of your end step, if you control a creature with power 5 or greater, you may draw a card.\n{T}: Add {C} to your mana pool.
flavor: "I feel the vine-rhythm as my friends drive the beast to me. I will not miss my mark."

name: Elvish Skysweeper
text: {4}{G}, Sacrifice a creature: Destroy target creature with flying.
flavor: The spires of Ravnica are no different from the tall trees of other planes. The elves navigate and protect them just the same.

name: Farhaven Elf
text: When Farhaven Elf enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic land card and put it onto the battlefield tapped. If you do, shuffle your library.
flavor: "Verdant bloom does exist. It merely hides for its own safety."

name: Fecundity
text: Whenever a creature dies, that creature's controller may draw a card.
flavor: Life is eternal. A lifetime is ephemeral.

name: Foster
text: Whenever a creature you control dies, you may pay {1}. If you do, reveal cards from the top of your library until you reveal a creature card. Put that card into your hand and the rest into your graveyard.

name: Grazing Gladehart
text: Landfall — Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, you may gain 2 life.
flavor: "Don't be fooled. If it were as docile as it looks, it would've died off long ago."\n—Yon Basrel, Oran-Rief survivalist

name: Harmonize
text: Draw three cards.
flavor: "Words lie. People lie. The land tells the truth."

name: Hua Tuo, Honored Physician
text: {T}: Put target creature card from your graveyard on top of your library. Activate this ability only during your turn, before attackers are declared.

name: Hunted Troll
text: When Hunted Troll enters the battlefield, target opponent puts four 1/1 blue Faerie creature tokens with flying onto the battlefield.\n{G}: Regenerate Hunted Troll.

name: Jade Mage
text: {2}{G}: Put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: "We are one with the wild things. Life blooms from our fingertips and nature responds to our summons."\n—Jade creed

name: Kazandu Tuskcaller
text:
Level up {1}{G} ({1}{G}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 2-5
1/1
{T}: Put a 3/3 green Elephant creature token onto the battlefield.
LEVEL 6+
1/1
{T}: Put two 3/3 green Elephant creature tokens onto the battlefield.

name: Krosan Grip
text: Split second (As long as this spell is on the stack, players can't cast spells or activate abilities that aren't mana abilities.)\nDestroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: "Give up these unnatural weapons, these scrolls. Heart and mind and fist are enough."\n—Zyd, Kamahlite druid

name: Krosan Tusker
text: Cycling {2}{G} ({2}{G}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nWhen you cycle Krosan Tusker, you may search your library for a basic land card, reveal that card, put it into your hand, then shuffle your library.

name: Krosan Warchief
text: Beast spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.\n{1}{G}: Regenerate target Beast.
flavor: It turns prey into predator.

name: Mold Shambler
text: Kicker {1}{G} (You may pay an additional {1}{G} as you cast this spell.)\nWhen Mold Shambler enters the battlefield, if it was kicked, destroy target noncreature permanent.
flavor: When civilization encroaches on nature, Zendikar encroaches back.

name: Naya Soulbeast
text: Trample\nWhen you cast Naya Soulbeast, each player reveals the top card of his or her library. Naya Soulbeast enters the battlefield with X +1/+1 counters on it, where X is the total converted mana cost of all cards revealed this way.

name: Night Soil
text: {1}, Exile two creature cards from a single graveyard: Put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: Some said killing the thallids only encouraged them.

name: One Dozen Eyes
text:
Choose one —
• Put a 5/5 green Beast creature token onto the battlefield.
• Put five 1/1 green Insect creature tokens onto the battlefield.
Entwine {G}{G}{G} (Choose both if you pay the entwine cost.)

name: Phantom Nantuko
text:
Trample
Phantom Nantuko enters the battlefield with two +1/+1 counters on it.
If damage would be dealt to Phantom Nantuko, prevent that damage. Remove a +1/+1 counter from Phantom Nantuko.
{T}: Put a +1/+1 counter on Phantom Nantuko.

name: Presence of Gond
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has "{T}: Put a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token onto the battlefield."
flavor: "Here lies Gond, hero of Safehold Taldwen. May he ever guide our quest."

name: Primal Vigor
text: If one or more tokens would be put onto the battlefield, twice that many of those tokens are put onto the battlefield instead.\nIf one or more +1/+1 counters would be placed on a creature, twice that many +1/+1 counters are placed on that creature instead.

name: Rain of Thorns
text:
Choose one or more —
• Destroy target artifact.
• Destroy target enchantment.
• Destroy target land.
flavor: When the forests became havens for evil, the archmages devised new ways to cleanse the wilds.

name: Rampaging Baloths
text: Trample\nLandfall — Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, you may put a 4/4 green Beast creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: "When the land is angry, so are they."\n—Nissa Revane

name: Ravenous Baloth
text: Sacrifice a Beast: You gain 4 life.
flavor: "All we know about the Krosan Forest we have learned from those few who made it out alive."\n—Elvish refugee

name: Reincarnation
text: Choose target creature. When that creature dies this turn, return a creature card from its owner's graveyard to the battlefield under the control of that creature's owner.
flavor: "You cannot imagine what eyes you may look through tomorrow."\n—Aerona, elder druid

name: Restore
text: Put target land card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.
flavor: "See, the land itself raises an altar to the ascendancy of nature."\n—Mayael the Anima

name: Sakura-Tribe Elder
text: Sacrifice Sakura-Tribe Elder: Search your library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
flavor: Slain warriors were buried with a tree sapling, so they would become a part of the forest after death.

name: Silklash Spider
text: Reach\n{X}{G}{G}: Silklash Spider deals X damage to each creature with flying.
flavor: By the time the spider comes to slurp up its dinner, its victims have been partially dissolved by acidic silk.

name: Slice in Twain
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.\nDraw a card.
flavor: "The hypocrisy of these elves is thicker than steel—destroying ‘unnatural metal' with their own enchanted swords."\n—Kara Vrist, Neurok agent

name: Spawning Grounds
text: Enchant land\nEnchanted land has "{T}: Put a 5/5 green Beast creature token with trample onto the battlefield."
flavor: It's the only water source in miles of desert, but the local tribes avoid it at all costs.

name: Spoils of Victory
text: Search your library for a Plains, Island, Swamp, Mountain, or Forest card and put that card onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.

name: Sprouting Vines
text: Search your library for a basic land card, reveal that card, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.\nStorm (When you cast this spell, copy it for each spell cast before it this turn.)

name: Tempt with Discovery
text: Tempting offer — Search your library for a land card and put it onto the battlefield. Each opponent may search his or her library for a land card and put it onto the battlefield. For each opponent who searches a library this way, search your library for a land card and put it onto the battlefield. Then each player who searched a library this way shuffles it.

name: Walker of the Grove
text: When Walker of the Grove leaves the battlefield, put a 4/4 green Elemental creature token onto the battlefield.\nEvoke {4}{G} (You may cast this spell for its evoke cost. If you do, it's sacrificed when it enters the battlefield.)

name: Æthermage's Touch
text: Reveal the top four cards of your library. You may put a creature card from among them onto the battlefield. It gains "At the beginning of your end step, return this creature to its owner's hand." Then put the rest of the cards revealed this way on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Baleful Strix
text: Flying, deathtouch\nWhen Baleful Strix enters the battlefield, draw a card.
flavor: Its beak rends flesh and bone, exposing the tender marrow of dream.

name: Behemoth Sledge
text: Equipped creature gets +2/+2 and has lifelink and trample.\nEquip {3}
flavor: Those who worship the great gargantuans could hardly be expected to fight with a subtle weapon.

name: Boros Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Boros Charm deals 4 damage to target player.
• Permanents you control gain indestructible until end of turn.
• Target creature gains double strike until end of turn.
flavor: "Practice compassion and mercy. But know when they must end."\n—Aurelia

name: Charnelhoard Wurm
text: Trample\nWhenever Charnelhoard Wurm deals damage to an opponent, you may return target card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Jund's dragons hoard only sangrite crystals. Its wurms aren't so picky.

name: Crosis's Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Return target permanent to its owner's hand.
• Destroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.
• Destroy target artifact.
flavor: A pretty bauble of persecution.

name: Cruel Ultimatum
text: Target opponent sacrifices a creature, discards three cards, then loses 5 life. You return a creature card from your graveyard to your hand, draw three cards, then gain 5 life.
flavor: There is always a greater power.

name: Death Grasp
text: Death Grasp deals X damage to target creature or player. You gain X life.
flavor: Plate mail, the skin of the chest, the rib cage, the heart—all useless against the mage who can reach directly for the soul.

name: Deathbringer Thoctar
text: Whenever another creature dies, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Deathbringer Thoctar.\nRemove a +1/+1 counter from Deathbringer Thoctar: Deathbringer Thoctar deals 1 damage to target creature or player.

name: Deepfire Elemental
text: {X}{X}{1}: Destroy target artifact or creature with converted mana cost X.
flavor: "There are deep, deep places in this world that have long burned hot with little regard for the whitening of the earth's thin skin."\n—Sek'Kuar, Deathkeeper

name: Derevi, Empyrial Tactician
text: Flying\nWhenever Derevi, Empyrial Tactician enters the battlefield or a creature you control deals combat damage to a player, you may tap or untap target permanent.\n{1}{G}{W}{U}: Put Derevi onto the battlefield from the command zone.

name: Dromar's Charm
text:
Choose one —
• You gain 5 life.
• Counter target spell.
• Target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor: "Wisdom can be summed up in two rules: Control what you can. Eliminate what you cannot."\n—Dromar, the Banisher

name: Fiery Justice
text: Fiery Justice deals 5 damage divided as you choose among any number of target creatures and/or players. Target opponent gains 5 life.
flavor: When the rebels couldn't breach the castle to kill Lalor the Obstinate, they tried a more internal approach to depose the pretender king.

name: Filigree Angel
text: Flying\nWhen Filigree Angel enters the battlefield, you gain 3 life for each artifact you control.
flavor: "I craved enlightenment, and Crucius's etherium opened my eyes. I would share my sight with you, but first you must believe."

name: Fires of Yavimaya
text: Creatures you control have haste.\nSacrifice Fires of Yavimaya: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: Yavimaya lights the quickest path to battle.

name: Gahiji, Honored One
text: Whenever a creature attacks one of your opponents or a planeswalker an opponent controls, that creature gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: He can stir the gentlest spirit to wild ferocity.

name: Grixis Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Return target permanent to its owner's hand.
• Target creature gets -4/-4 until end of turn.
• Creatures you control get +2/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: "So many choices. Shall I choose loathing, hate, or malice today?"\n—Eliza of the Keep

name: Hull Breach
text:
Choose one —
• Destroy target artifact.
• Destroy target enchantment.
• Destroy target artifact and target enchantment.
flavor: "Crovax knows we're coming now," said a grinning Sisay. "I just sent the Predator crashing into his stronghold."

name: Jeleva, Nephalia's Scourge
text: Flying\nWhen Jeleva, Nephalia's Scourge enters the battlefield, each player exiles the top X cards of his or her library, where X is the amount of mana spent to cast Jeleva.\nWhenever Jeleva attacks, you may cast an instant or sorcery card exiled with it without paying its mana cost.

name: Jund Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Exile all cards from target player's graveyard.
• Jund Charm deals 2 damage to each creature.
• Put two +1/+1 counters on target creature.
flavor: Jund pulses with raw energy, waiting for shamans to shape it into useful form.

name: Leafdrake Roost
text: Enchant land\nEnchanted land has "{G}{U}, {T}: Put a 2/2 green and blue Drake creature token with flying onto the battlefield."
flavor: "The best experiments are those whose successes replicate themselves."\n—Yolov, Simic bioengineer

name: Lim-Dûl's Vault
text: Look at the top five cards of your library. As many times as you choose, you may pay 1 life, put those cards on the bottom of your library in any order, then look at the top five cards of your library. Then shuffle your library and put the last cards you looked at this way on top of it in any order.

name: Marath, Will of the Wild
text:
Marath, Will of the Wild enters the battlefield with a number of +1/+1 counters on it equal to the amount of mana spent to cast it.
{X}, Remove X +1/+1 counters from Marath: Choose one —
• Put X +1/+1 counters on target creature. X can't be 0.
• Marath deals X damage to target creature or player. X can't be 0.
• Put an X/X green Elemental creature token onto the battlefield. X can't be 0.

name: Mayael the Anima
text: {3}{R}{G}{W}, {T}: Look at the top five cards of your library. You may put a creature card with power 5 or greater from among them onto the battlefield. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.
flavor: The sacred Anima's eyes are blind to all but the grandest truths.

name: Naya Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Naya Charm deals 3 damage to target creature.
• Return target card from a graveyard to its owner's hand.
• Tap all creatures target player controls.
flavor: Deep in nature's core lies a potential unsullied by greed or civilization.

name: Nekusar, the Mindrazer
text: At the beginning of each player's draw step, that player draws an additional card.\nWhenever an opponent draws a card, Nekusar, the Mindrazer deals 1 damage to that player.
flavor: His enemies wondered if the lich king's brutal death and unnatural rebirth had been his plan all along.

name: Nivix Guildmage
text: {1}{U}{R}: Draw a card, then discard a card.\n{2}{U}{R}: Copy target instant or sorcery spell you control. You may choose new targets for the copy.
flavor: "The only action worth taking is one with an unknown outcome."

name: Oloro, Ageless Ascetic
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you gain 2 life.\nWhenever you gain life, you may pay {1}. If you do, draw a card and each opponent loses 1 life.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, if Oloro, Ageless Ascetic is in the command zone, you gain 2 life.

name: Prossh, Skyraider of Kher
text: Flying\nWhen you cast Prossh, Skyraider of Kher, put X 0/1 red Kobold creature tokens named Kobolds of Kher Keep onto the battlefield, where X is the amount of mana spent to cast Prossh.\nSacrifice another creature: Prossh gets +1/+0 until end of turn.

name: Rakeclaw Gargantuan
text: {1}: Target creature with power 5 or greater gains first strike until end of turn.
flavor: Naya teems with gargantuans, titanic monsters to whom both nature and civilization defer.

name: Roon of the Hidden Realm
text: Vigilance, trample\n{2}, {T}: Exile another target creature. Return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control at the beginning of the next end step.
flavor: "Time and space are just new battlefields to be mastered."

name: Rubinia Soulsinger
text: You may choose not to untap Rubinia Soulsinger during your untap step.\n{T}: Gain control of target creature for as long as you control Rubinia and Rubinia remains tapped.
flavor: "Take up the quill, and feel your future flow into the runes."

name: Savage Twister
text: Savage Twister deals X damage to each creature.
flavor: "Nature is the ultimate mindless destroyer, capable of power and ferocity no army can match, and the Gruul follow its example."\n—Trigori, Azorius senator

name: Scarland Thrinax
text: Sacrifice a creature: Put a +1/+1 counter on Scarland Thrinax.
flavor: "There is only one way of life in Jund: feed on the weak until you are cut down by something stronger."\n—Jorshu of Clan Nel Toth

name: Sek'Kuar, Deathkeeper
text: Whenever another nontoken creature you control dies, put a 3/1 black and red Graveborn creature token with haste onto the battlefield.
flavor: The orcs believe Sek'Kuar still lives in the Karplusan Mountains, gathering his dead army, intent on revenge.

name: Selesnya Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Target creature gets +2/+2 and gains trample until end of turn.
• Exile target creature with power 5 or greater.
• Put a 2/2 white Knight creature token with vigilance onto the battlefield.

name: Sharuum the Hegemon
text: Flying\nWhen Sharuum the Hegemon enters the battlefield, you may return target artifact card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: To gain audience with the hegemon, one must bring a riddle she has not heard.

name: Shattergang Brothers
text: {2}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Each other player sacrifices a creature.\n{2}{R}, Sacrifice an artifact: Each other player sacrifices an artifact.\n{2}{G}, Sacrifice an enchantment: Each other player sacrifices an enchantment.

name: Skyward Eye Prophets
text: Vigilance\n{T}: Reveal the top card of your library. If it's a land card, put it onto the battlefield. Otherwise, put it into your hand.
flavor: They lament the doom that is coming to Bant without realizing the part their own leaders have played in it.

name: Soul Manipulation
text: Choose one or both —\n• Counter target creature spell.\n• Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: "Birth and death are both reversible."\n—Nicol Bolas

name: Spellbreaker Behemoth
text: Spellbreaker Behemoth can't be countered.\nCreature spells you control with power 5 or greater can't be countered.
flavor: "Some think its immunity to countermagic evolved because of the constant mage attacks on Naya. I think it just ate a bunch of wizards."\n—Broka, drumhunter

name: Sphinx of the Steel Wind
text: Flying, first strike, vigilance, lifelink, protection from red and from green
flavor: No one has properly answered her favorite riddle: "Why should I spare your life?"

name: Spinal Embrace
text: Cast Spinal Embrace only during combat.\nUntap target creature you don't control and gain control of it. It gains haste until end of turn. At the beginning of the next end step, sacrifice it. If you do, you gain life equal to its toughness.

name: Sprouting Thrinax
text: When Sprouting Thrinax dies, put three 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: The vast network of predation on Jund has actually caused some strange creatures to adapt to being eaten.

name: Sydri, Galvanic Genius
text: {U}: Target noncreature artifact becomes an artifact creature with power and toughness each equal to its converted mana cost until end of turn.\n{W}{B}: Target artifact creature gains deathtouch and lifelink until end of turn.

name: Thraximundar
text: Haste\nWhenever Thraximundar attacks, defending player sacrifices a creature.\nWhenever a player sacrifices a creature, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Thraximundar.
flavor: His name means "he who paints the earth red."

name: Tidehollow Strix
text: Flying\nDeathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
flavor: The scullers beneath Esper keep strixes as trained pets, and set them loose when a fare refuses to pay.

name: Tower Gargoyle
text: Flying
flavor: "Esper, like any work of art, can be truly appreciated only from a distance."\n—Tezzeret

name: Valley Rannet
text: Mountaincycling {2}, forestcycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Search your library for a Mountain or Forest card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.)

name: Vizkopa Guildmage
text: {1}{W}{B}: Target creature gains lifelink until end of turn.\n{1}{W}{B}: Whenever you gain life this turn, each opponent loses that much life.

name: Winged Coatl
text: Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)\nFlying\nDeathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
flavor: The nacatl called this new species "vetli," their word for poison arrows.

name: Augury Adept
text: Whenever Augury Adept deals combat damage to a player, reveal the top card of your library and put that card into your hand. You gain life equal to its converted mana cost.
flavor: Moonstones grant limited foresight but unlimited advantages.

name: Divinity of Pride
text: Flying, lifelink\nDivinity of Pride gets +4/+4 as long as you have 25 or more life.
flavor: "She spoke of mystery and portent, of such unfathomable things that my mind screamed for pity."\n—The Seer's Parables

name: Golgari Guildmage
text: {4}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.\n{4}{G}: Put a +1/+1 counter on target creature.

name: Mistmeadow Witch
text: {2}{W}{U}: Exile target creature. Return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control at the beginning of the next end step.
flavor: Olka collected the evening mist for years, studying its secrets. Once she learned its essence, she could vanish with a thought.

name: Murkfiend Liege
text: Other green creatures you control get +1/+1.\nOther blue creatures you control get +1/+1.\nUntap all green and/or blue creatures you control during each other player's untap step.

name: Selesnya Guildmage
text: {3}{G}: Put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield.\n{3}{W}: Creatures you control get +1/+1 until end of turn.

name: Spiteful Visions
text: At the beginning of each player's draw step, that player draws an additional card.\nWhenever a player draws a card, Spiteful Visions deals 1 damage to that player.
flavor: Knowledge brings the sting of disillusionment, but the pain teaches perspective.

name: Thopter Foundry
text: {1}, Sacrifice a nontoken artifact: Put a 1/1 blue Thopter artifact creature token with flying onto the battlefield. You gain 1 life.
flavor: "Etherium is limited. Innovation is not."\n—Tezzeret

name: Armillary Sphere
text: {2}, {T}, Sacrifice Armillary Sphere: Search your library for up to two basic land cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: The mysterious purpose of two of the rings had eluded Esper mages—until now.

name: Azorius Keyrune
text: {T}: Add {W} or {U} to your mana pool.\n{W}{U}: Azorius Keyrune becomes a 2/2 white and blue Bird artifact creature with flying until end of turn.
flavor: "The higher the mind soars, the greater its understanding of the law."\n—Isperia

name: Basalt Monolith
text: Basalt Monolith doesn't untap during your untap step.\n{T}: Add {C}{C}{C} to your mana pool.\n{3}: Untap Basalt Monolith.

name: Carnage Altar
text: {3}, Sacrifice a creature: Draw a card.
flavor: "In these bloodstains I will find the fingerprints of our oppressors."\n—Anowon, the Ruin Sage

name: Conjurer's Closet
text: At the beginning of your end step, you may exile target creature you control, then return that card to the battlefield under your control.
flavor: "Tomorrow wears yesterday's face."\n—Kordel the Cryptic

name: Crawlspace
text: No more than two creatures can attack you each combat.
flavor: Lord Rondor arrived for battle with sixty war elephants, ten catapults, and two hundred of his finest archers. Then he saw the battlefield . . .

name: Darksteel Ingot
text: Indestructible\n{T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.
flavor: "It reflects the purity of Mirrodin-that-was."\n—Koth of the Hammer
